Gratuity refers to a sum of money given voluntarily by an individual or organization to express appreciation or gratitude for a service rendered. It is typically provided in addition to the agreed-upon payment or salary. Gratuity is often given in occupations such as hospitality, food service, personal services, or any other field where tipping is customary.
